    <h1>About NearMates</h1>

    <p>
      Human connection has always been at the center of our lives. But when people move to a new place, they often feel disconnected from their passions, hobbies, and the communities they once enjoyed. This project has been designed with a very clear goal: 
      to bring together individuals who share the same interests and make it easy for them to connect, collaborate, and create meaningful relationships. 
      Whether it is sports, music, art, travel, coding, or simply casual hobbies — this platform ensures that nobody feels left out when they move to a new city or neighborhood. 
    </p>

    <h2>Core Vision of the Platform</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Interest-Based Networking:</strong> People don’t just want random social connections; they want meaningful connections with those who share the same passion. This platform builds communities around hobbies and activities.</li>
      <li><strong>Reducing Loneliness:</strong> Many individuals feel isolated when shifting to a new environment. By joining groups and meeting like-minded individuals, they instantly feel at home.</li>
      <li><strong>Encouraging Collaboration:</strong> From forming a local football team to creating a coding club, the platform gives people the tools to turn ideas into real activities.</li>
      <li><strong>Safe & Inclusive Environment:</strong> Designed to prioritize digital safety, user privacy, and respectful communication.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Why This Project is Needed</h2>
    <p>
      Imagine moving to a completely new city. You want to play badminton, but you don’t know anyone around. Or perhaps you are passionate about photography but have no clue where to find a community of photographers nearby. 
      In such cases, most people end up leaving their passions behind. This platform solves that exact problem by showing you who around you shares the same interest. 
      You can directly connect with them, chat, form groups, and start engaging in your hobbies again — without waiting for months to discover people organically.
    </p>

